},{"title":"Author/Béatrice Ferrari","target":"Author/Béatrice Ferrari","line":138},{"title":"Author/Beatrice Ferrari","target":"Author/Beatrice Ferrari","line":139},{"title":"Author/Alessandra Occhinegro","target":"Author/Alessandra Occhinegro","line":140},{"title":"Author/A. Occhinegro","target":"Author/A. Occhinegro","line":141},{"title":"Author/Carmine Di Iorio","target":"Author/Carmine Di Iorio","line":142},{"title":"Author/Carmine Di Iorio","target":"Author/Carmine Di Iorio","line":143},{"title":"Author/Fabrizio De Luca","target":"Author/Fabrizio De Luca","line":144},{"title":"Author/Fabrizio De Luca","target":"Author/Fabrizio De Luca","line":145},{"title":"Author/Valentina Cesaroni","target":"Author/Valentina Cesaroni","line":146},{"title":"Author/Valentina Cesaroni","target":"Author/Valentina Cesaroni","line":147},{"title":"Author/Carolina Elena Girometta","target":"Author/Carolina Elena Girometta","line":148},{"title":"Author/Carolina Girometta","target":"Author/Carolina Girometta","line":149},{"title":"Author/Maria Grazia Bottone","target":"Author/Maria Grazia Bottone","line":150},{"title":"Author/Maria Grazia Bottone","target":"Author/Maria Grazia Bottone","line":151},{"title":"Author/Elena Savino","target":"Author/Elena Savino","line":152},{"title":"Author/Elena Savino","target":"Author/Elena Savino","line":153},{"title":"Author/Hirokazu Kawagishi","target":"Author/Hirokazu Kawagishi","line":154},{"title":"Author/Hirokazu Kawagishi","target":"Author/Hirokazu Kawagishi","line":155},{"title":"Author/Hirokazu Kawagishi","target":"Author/Hirokazu Kawagishi","line":156},{"title":"Author/Paola Rossi","target":"Author/Paola Rossi","line":157},{"title":"Author/Paola Rossi","target":"Author/Paola Rossi","line":158},{"title":"Author/Paola Rossi","target":"Author/Paola Rossi","line":159},{"title":"Author/Paola Rossi","target":"Author/Paola Rossi","line":160},{"title":"PDF","target":"biblib/ratto_hericium_2019/ratto_hericium_2019.pdf","line":162}],"metadata":{"id":"ratto_hericium_2019","type":"article-journal","title":"Hericium erinaceus Improves Recognition Memory and Induces Hippocampal and Cerebellar Neurogenesis in Frail Mice during Aging","issued":{"date-parts":[[2019]]},"DOI":"10.3390/nu11040715","container-title":"Nutrients","abstract":"Frailty is a geriatric syndrome associated with both locomotor and cognitive decline, implicated in both poor quality of life and negative health outcomes. One central question surrounding frailty is whether phenotypic frailty is associated with the cognitive impairment during aging. Using spontaneous behavioral tests and by studying the dynamic change during aging, we demonstrated that the two form of vulnerability, locomotor and recognition memory decline, develop in parallel and therefore, integration of the motoric and cognitive evaluations are imperative. We developed an integrated frailty index based on both phenotypic and recognition memory performances. Hericium erinaceus (H. erinaceus) is a medicinal mushroom that improves recognition memory in mice. By using HPLC-UV-ESI/MS analyses we obtained standardized amounts of erinacine A and hericenones C and D in H. erinaceus extracts, that were tested in our animal model of physiological aging. Two-month oral supplementation with H. erinaceus reversed the age-decline of recognition memory. Proliferating cell nuclear antigen (PCNA) and doublecortin (DCX) immunohistochemistry in the hippocampus and cerebellum in treated mice supported a positive effect of an H. erinaceus on neurogenesis in frail mice.","tags":["#literature_note"],"author":[{"family":"Ratto","given":"Daniela","literal":""},{"family":"Ratto","given":"Daniela","literal":""},{"family":"Corana","given":"Federica","literal":""},{"family":"Corana","given":"Federica","literal":""},{"family":"Mannucci","given":"Barbara","literal":""},{"family":"Mannucci","given":"Barbara","literal":""},{"family":"Priori","given":"Erica Cecilia","literal":""},{"family":"Priori","given":"Erica Cecilia","literal":""},{"family":"Cobelli","given":"Filippo","literal":""},{"family":"Cobelli","given":"Filippo","literal":""},{"family":"Roda","given":"Elisa","literal":""},{"family":"Roda","given":"Elisa","literal":""},{"family":"Ferrari","given":"Béatrice","literal":""},{"family":"Ferrari","given":"Beatrice","literal":""},{"family":"Occhinegro","given":"Alessandra","literal":""},{"family":"Occhinegro","given":"A.","literal":""},{"family":"Iorio","given":"Carmine Di","literal":""},{"family":"Iorio","given":"Carmine Di","literal":""},{"family":"Luca","given":"Fabrizio De","literal":""},{"family":"Luca","given":"Fabrizio De","literal":""},{"family":"Cesaroni","given":"Valentina","literal":""},{"family":"Cesaroni","given":"Valentina","literal":""},{"family":"Girometta","given":"Carolina Elena","literal":""},{"family":"Girometta","given":"Carolina","literal":""},{"family":"Bottone","given":"Maria Grazia","literal":""},{"family":"Bottone","given":"Maria Grazia","literal":""},{"family":"Savino","given":"Elena","literal":""},{"family":"Savino","given":"Elena","literal":""},{"family":"Kawagishi","given":"Hirokazu","literal":""},{"family":"Kawagishi","given":"Hirokazu","literal":""},{"family":"Kawagishi","given":"Hirokazu","literal":""},{"family":"Rossi","given":"Paola","literal":""},{"family":"Rossi","given":"Paola","literal":""},{"family":"Rossi","given":"Paola","literal":""},{"family":"Rossi","given":"Paola","literal":""}],"citation-key":"ratto_hericium_2019","year":"2019","dateCreated":"2026-03-31","reading-status":"to-read","aliases":["Hericium erinaceus Improves Recognition Memory and Induces Hippocampal and Cerebellar Neurogenesis in Frail Mice during Aging"],"author-links":["[[Author/Daniela Ratto]]","[[Author/Daniela Ratto]]","[[Author/Federica Corana]]","[[Author/Federica Corana]]","[[Author/Barbara Mannucci]]","[[Author/Barbara Mannucci]]","[[Author/Erica Cecilia Priori]]","[[Author/Erica Cecilia Priori]]","[[Author/Filippo Cobelli]]","[[Author/Filippo Cobelli]]","